{"word":"H29 - אֲבִיָּה - ʼĂbîyâh - ab-ee-yaw' - Abiah","slug":"H29","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֲבִיָּה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼĂbîyâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ab-ee-yaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Abiah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>אביּהוּ אביּה</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>'ăbı̂yâh 'ăbı̂yâhû</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>ab-ee-yaw'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Abia or Abiah or Abijah = \"Jehovah is (my) father\" <ol><li>king of Judah, son and successor of Rehoboam</li><li>second son of Samuel</li><li>son of Jeroboam the first, king of Israel</li><li>son of Becher, a Benjamite</li><li>head of a priestly house (one of the 24 Levite groups)</li><li>head of a priestly house (after the exile)</li><li>wife of Hezron</li><li>mother of Hezekiah (compare <u><a href=\"#/H21\">H21</a></u>)</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H1\">H1</a> and <a href=\"#/H3050\">H3050</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1\">H1</a>, <a href=\"#/H21\">H21</a>, <a href=\"#/H22\">H22</a>, <a href=\"#/H23\">H23</a>, <a href=\"#/H26\">H26</a>, <a href=\"#/H27\">H27</a>, <a href=\"#/H28\">H28</a>, <a href=\"#/H30\">H30</a>, <a href=\"#/H31\">H31</a>, <a href=\"#/H32\">H32</a>, <a href=\"#/H33\">H33</a>, <a href=\"#/H36\">H36</a>, <a href=\"#/H37\">H37</a>, <a href=\"#/H372\">H372</a>, <a href=\"#/H373\">H373</a>, <a href=\"#/H38\">H38</a>, <a href=\"#/H39\">H39</a>, <a href=\"#/H40\">H40</a>, <a href=\"#/H41\">H41</a>, <a href=\"#/H42\">H42</a>, <a href=\"#/H43\">H43</a>, <a href=\"#/H44\">H44</a>, <a href=\"#/H45\">H45</a>, <a href=\"#/H48\">H48</a>, <a href=\"#/H49\">H49</a>, <a href=\"#/H50\">H50</a>, <a href=\"#/H51\">H51</a>, <a href=\"#/H52\">H52</a>, <a href=\"#/H53\">H53</a>, <a href=\"#/H